Troops of Nigerian Army’s 222 Battalion deployed in Operation Lafiya Dole on Sunday killed two Boko Haram terrorists while on an ambush operation around Malari village in  Borno State while others fleed into the bush.
The troops recovered ten bicycles from the terrorists during the encounter.
In a statement signed by the Director of Army Public Relations, Brigadier General Texas Chukwu, he called on the public to report any suspicious movements or activities to security agents for necessary action.